The expansive space of Level 359 most notably resembles a zoo, and is the 360<sup>th</sup> level of the Backrooms. It has dirt trails extending in all directions with empty exhibits at overpasses, only breaking the monotony with unattended carts for every 100 feet or so. It's dirt pathways stop and start at bridges extending over ponds, showcasing signs depicting frontroom animals, despite the inherit lack of animals throughout the Backrooms. In Level 359's dimly lit halls, various water tanks emit a deep hue of blue, and it's exhibits filled with plant life defiantly persist despite the apparent lack of care. Many wanderers describe tall, limestone covered walls upon entering, with anything from metal fencing to clear glass windows Hyperbolica provides a calm atmosphere to wanderers alike with it's familiar sense of wonder.</div>
<span style= "font-family:Aleo; text-shadow: 1.5px 1.5px 0px #000000, 1px 1px 10px #45392d, 0px 0px 1px #000000; font-size:36px; color:white"><center>'''Description'''</center></span>
{{Underline|#FFFFF}}
{{Blurimage|file=Levelh1.jpg|caption='''A photograph of the Aquatic Exhibits within Hyperbolica'''}}
'''Level 359''', otherwise known as "'''Hyperbolica'''," is an infinite, non-euclidean space, often stated to be an "endless zoo," with dirt trails interconnecting to many unique buildings, some housing exhibits of all varieties, and others serving only as housing or resting spaces. '''Level 359''' has a perpetual night sky with a dense fog, requiring a sufficient light source for darker regions of the level.<ref>Level 359 is devoid of any diurnal cycles.
</ref> The dirt paths around '''Level 359''' are lined with wood cabins at some sections, and these cabins serve as the main sanctuaries in '''Hyperbolica'''. The cabins have hard wood floors, and clear glass windows. Tables and chairs are laid out near a fireplace, often with a warm cup of Almond Tea already resting on a table cloth. One or more beds are always situated in one of the cabin's corners, with a desk and lamp sat nearby. Bags can sometimes be found in these cabins, containing tools and valuables like batteries, flashlights, lighters, canteens, and objects, like Greek Fire and Almonds. The variety of useful objects and resources in '''Level 359''' make it a target of organizations seeking to obtain valuable resources, such as the M.E.G or Backroom Colonists. The many objects that can also be found in '''Level 359''' include Almonds, Moth Jelly, and many varients of Almond Water that are found throughout.

Some groups have been known to frequent '''Level 359''' for more miscellaneous purposes, such as Backrooms Today, whose personnel have been said to frequently visit the level seeking a calm and remote place to practice their journalism. The D.E.E.P. organization has visited '''Level 359''' with the goal to study the unique properties of plant life within '''Level 359'''<nowiki/>'s smaller enclosures. And most notably, the Entity Research Comittee or E.R.T. has launched investigations in cooperation with the M.E.G. and other scientific associations in order to start a file on an entity of interest within '''Level 359'''.

Some entities are known to prowl in the level's darker regions situated outside of most pathways, which pose a significant threat, but wanderers keeping a low profile will typically avoid any frequent encounters with the undesirables. Although the entities of '''Level 359''' tend not to be a profound threat to wanderers, '''Hyperbolica''', as it's name suggests, takes on a hyperbolic geometry that can warp the space of the level greatly depending on several factors. The curvature of the level's space has been observed to change as one explores further in the level. 

