At the point of origin where a wanderer enters '''Level 359''', the space will appear locally Euclidean, but as a person travels farther from this origin, the space's curvature will become much more apparent, causing a subtle fisheye view. This fisheye distortion will become more exaggerated the further someone explores. It is ill-advised to explore further than 30 kilometers, as by this point, the distortion in Level 359's hyperbolic space can create a confusing topology that will lead anyone without an intuitive sense of the Level's spacial geometry to become lost. 

The level's geometry could be considered manageable for the first 40 kilometers for an experienced wanderer with a scientific and intuitive knowledge of hyperbolic space, but it gradually adopts a more extreme curvature that can quickly morph into a dead-zone. Inexperienced wanderers who cross the point of no return will often perish after sustaining life-threatening injuries from spacial tidal forces after wandering too far. 

Symptoms of hyperbolic tidal forces vary based on the intensity of local curvature, but between the point of 15-30 kilometers, wanderers may feel slight tingling in their fingertips. At 30-40 kilometers, one can expect to experience tingling sensations in the tongue, lips, and fingertips, and even some numbness. At 40-50 kilometers, wanderers will experience headaches and loss of balance on top of an increase of the previous symptoms, including a metallic taste in their mouth. While there have not been many known to ever pass 50 kilometers, it can be assumed that passing this point will quickly result in seizures caused by subtle to severe brain damage, and that progress would halt completely without the ability to coordinate. 

Hyperbolica's spacial geometry poses many threats, that if not respected, can often result in a fatality, but it still includes many amenities that make it an excellent resting stop for any wanderers willing to take the extra steps to stay safe while tending to wounds, recovering from sickness, or even simply wishing to relax before continuing to other levels. Here's a catalogue of the different sectors that can be found within Hyperbolica.


