==Limestone Exhibits==

Wanderers who enter '''Level 359''' will often be treated to large, open-roof corridors made of limestone. These corridors fork in many directions, showcasing many exhibits that are barricaded or sealed by iron bars, gates, or durable glass panes. The exhibits do not contain any animals, but still have a wide range of habitats within them, containing plant life, earthly terrain, and water deposits within them. Many exhibits are entered through unlocked gates, and house numerous natural resources.  Fertile soil, that can used to grow crops in off-level outposts. These exhibits are also often larger on the inside than on the outside, sometimes containing hidden layers that can be discovered by walking around certain objects or walls.<ref>Due to the complexity of hyperbolic geometry, it is easy to underestimate the true volume of a room. The exterior of enclosures may seem far smaller than their insides, and traversing around enclosures can feel like walking through different rooms overlapping the same space, this may lead to the room seemingly changing it's layout as you move through it, but this is essentially just walking into a different part of the enclosure, rather than the room's interior or exterior changing.
</ref> Outside the exhibits, signs can be found with cartoonish depictions of zoo animals and an ineligible font. Unmanned drink carts can be found spread throughout limestone corridors, stocked with Almond Soda.

==Aquatic Exhibits==

Walking around the dirt paths of '''Level 359''' may lead you to discover the Aquatic Exhibits off to the side of a hub of cabins. These buildings consist mainly of dimly lit halls with a metallic structure, and black marble floors. The area's hallways are illuminated only by an occasional overhead light with the endless array of blue-lit water tanks and white illuminated plant displays. Large open rooms can be entered through large, open metal doors. These large rooms are dotted with tables, chairs, a snack bar, and large cylindrical water tanks that flush the room in a dim, blue glow. Various beverages like Almond Soda, Tea, can be found sitting in various locations in the large rooms, with the occasional Almond Coffee sitting warm, on the edge of the snack bar.

==Dark Forest==

In the dark forest that surrounds the exterior of '''Level 359'''<nowiki/>'s pleasantries, entities prowl around, waiting for a chance to ambush wanderers who stray too far from the light. Where there's nothing but silence. No crickets, no flies. Nothing other than the slight rustles of the ones hidden in the dark. Those who see a white glow, off the side of the paths, had best turn back and don't look back; that hasn't got anything to do with you.

==Entities==

Smilers, Skin Stealers, Death Moths, and Hounds all remain situated around the Dark Forest, but rarely, Hounds or Skin Stealers will be found wandering darker trails.

==Entrances and Exits==

===Entrances===

Wanderers attempting to calculate the area of a triangle in [[Level Pi|Level π]] will be transported to '''Level 359''' through anomalous means.<ref>The entry of Level 359 through Level π follows a queue system similar to Level π's entry from the Hive, leading researchers to speculate that Level 359 may be part of a larger subset of undiscovered levels.
</ref>

Falling into the void while attempting to enter [[Level 361]] by any means will redirect wanderers to '''Level 359'''

===Exits===

Those who rest near an angel statue will find themselves waking in [[Level 180]]

It's rumored that a large set of wooden doors may lead to a new place, but the sheer volume of '''Level 359'''  makes it nearly impossible to verify this, as no meaningful explorations of where the doors lead has ever been conducted.

Entering a blue door with "EMPLOYEES ONLY" written on it sends one to [[Level 369]].

